  "body": "*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*:\r\n\r\n1:1 chat will show one amount (0.1 ETH) but another amount (0 ETH) was actually sent if use /send command and cancel signing transaction on Sent transaction screen. As a result, fields on the screen become editable and user can provide another amount, e.g. change 0.1 ETH to 0 ETH and after this sign transaction. Unfortunately, 1:1 will show initial amount 0.1 ETH.\r\n\r\nIt's also possible to edit fields Asset and Recipient\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nI see 2 options:\r\n1. user can't modify values if transaction was initiated from 1:1 chat or\r\n2. user can modify values but then 1:1 chat should show proper amount sent\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n1:1 chat shows wrong amount used for send transaction\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nfrom 00:20 https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8487381/sessions/4393923712/?accessToken=Uclx0lDmnfyCET2N6r5AfcH5YLM\r\n- Open status\r\n- open 1:1 chat\r\n- send 0.01 \r\n- on Send transaction screen tap  on Sign transaction to enter password\r\n- tap Cancel\r\n- check if fields Amount, Asset and Recipient are editable\r\n- change value in Amount to 0 and Sign transaction\r\n- check send message shown in the chat and transaction history\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly jun 13 and PR build for #4742 \r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8487381/sessions/4393923712/?accessToken=Uclx0lDmnfyCET2N6r5AfcH5YLM\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.19 (6054) @403</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
